A common problem caused by poor digital communication is sending unclear or unprofessional emails.
For example, a student might send an email to a professor without a proper subject line, greeting, or clear message. 
This can lead to confusion, delays in response, or even a negative impression.
In such situations, the issue could be avoided by following proper email etiquette. 
The email should include a clear subject, a respectful greeting, a well-structured message, and a polite closing.
Using formal language and clearly stating the purpose of the email is also important.
This task helped me understand the importance of professional communication in academic and professional environments.
It showed me that even small mistakes in digital communication can create misunderstandings, and proper etiquette plays a key role in effective communication.
